            <li>IP address (decimal and binary)</li>
            <li>Netmask address (decimal and binary)</li>
            <li>Network address (decimal and binary)</li>
            <li>Broadcast address (decimal and binary)</li>
            <li>First next subnet block available</li>
            <li>First and last usable IP addresses</li>
            <li>First usable IP address after the network address</li>
            <li>Last usable IP address before the broadcast address</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-green-50 p-6 rounded-lg mb-8">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Practical Example</h3>
      <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4">Let's calculate a subnet for a small office network:</p>
      <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg mb-4">
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-600">
          <li>IP Address: <code class="bg-gray-100 px-2 py-1 rounded">192.168.1.0</code></li>
